The starter project still ran normally on a Nexus 6P when the exception occurred.

- OS X El Capitan on a MacPro
- Android 7.0 on a Nexus 6P

@danrubel Might want to take a look at flutter tools.

**Repro steps:**
1. Create a new app from the terminal: `flutter create testapp`
2. Run it in prod mode from the terminal: `flutter run --release`

_Expected and actual result_: Runs with no error
1. Start IntelliJ
2. Create new project with File->New, pick Flutter, point it at the testapp dir
3. Click the Run ('Play' icon) button in the toolbar

_Expected result_: No error just like when running from the terminal
_Actual result_: All the errors mentioned above
@danrubel see above bug link, looks related?
We can close this one. The problem will no longer appear after https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/6280 is fixed.
